<p>In the latest development, U.S. Vice President J.D. Vance flew to Israel on Oct. 21 to press both sides to sustain a fragile Gaza ceasefire and to push U.S. plans for disarming Hamas and post-war reconstruction [nytimes.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. U.S. officials said the truce has shown progress despite weekend flare-ups of violence and Israeli airstrikes, and Vance urged patience while monitoring steps to recover hostages and their remains [npr.org#1][cbsnews.com#1]. Hamas returned two more bodies this week, bringing the number of deceased hostages returned to Israel to 15 of 28, and Israel identified the two most recent remains [bbc.com#1][theglobeandmail.com#1]. The visit included high-level meetings with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu as Washington tries to anchor a ceasefire that negotiators describe as fragile but workable [washingtonpost.com#1][nytimes.com#2].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/K4SP2vOtAVm2yvZWbmhNxpgu6fmk96sgQgrayfMTRWmpsEQMztbzN2QAzj0YcLTqqQ3qLIp_ShUqSkNXzSY8H1Q-wkp4KSMCV6mSFflHjjkCndkvnjTIpbjlQvs0_Xo7RL3AcmCSDiU0YrRHUZTKA1Lsoo9tRtZdssOGN0jbE7ZtOFFXJcULYNoegkEvmnQMLGuZZAC8' alt='Vice President J.D. Vance met with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in Jerusalem on Wednesday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>coordination centre: The United States helped open a joint U.S.-Israeli civil-military coordination centre in southwest Israel to monitor the truce and manage reconstruction tasks [newarab.com#1][theguardian.com#1].</li><li>timeline stance: Vance declined to set a firm deadline for when Hamas must disarm and said he was not in Israel to &#x27;babysit&#x27; the cease-fire, signaling a flexible U.S. approach [nytimes.com#2].</li><li>west bank unrest: Israeli settler violence in the West Bank has continued during the ceasefire, adding to regional tensions even as Gaza pauses major combat operations [dw.com#1].</li><li>us delegation: Those traveling with the U.S. team included President Trump&#x27;s envoy Steve Witkoff and Jared Kushner, underscoring the administration&#x27;s direct involvement in truce implementation [rt.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Going frankly better than I expected - Vice President J.D. Vance</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Vice President J.D. Vance: Vance expressed optimism that the ceasefire is making progress and urged patience while monitoring implementation and hostage recovery efforts. (<a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/22/nx-s1-5581401/vance-says-gaza-ceasefire-is-making-progress-despite-weekend-fighting'>NPR</a>)</li><li>Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu: Netanyahu emphasized identification and return of hostages&#x27; remains while stressing Israeli security needs during talks with the U.S. delegation. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2025/oct/22/israel-gaza-ceasefire-jd-vance-netanyahu-hamas-hostages-middle-east-latest-news-updates'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Hamas: Hamas warned that returning the remaining bodies and hostages will be difficult and said it needs time and technical assistance to find the missing under rubble. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/hamas-hands-over-remains-of-two-more-hostages-to-red-cross-in-gaza-israeli-military-says/article70187851.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>International Committee of the Red Cross: The Red Cross handled handovers of remains and facilitated transfers between Gaza and Israeli authorities as part of the ceasefire terms. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251022-two-more-israeli-hostage-bodies-returned-and-identified'>France 24</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/us-v-p-vance-says-tough-task-ahead-in-disarming-hamas'>US pushes plan to disarm Hamas and rebuild Gaza</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/22/nx-s1-5581401/vance-says-gaza-ceasefire-is-making-progress-despite-weekend-fighting'>Vance says Gaza ceasefire is making progress despite weekend fighting</a> - npr.org